- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper involves building a real-time makeup try-on demo.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as the paper involves rendering methods for the makeup try-on demo.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper involves developing models suitable for resource restricted devices, which is relevant to HCI.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves natural language processing in the form of a project page with more results and demo.
